      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Secondary QoIs include shear stress distribution and exposure time histograms, both directly informing hemolysis mechanism. QoI traceability matrix maps each model output to a clinical endpoint. Achieved Gradation 2 meets MRL 2 requirement."
