      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as used in the COU. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB range (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) used in experiments. Geometric fidelity confirmed by coordinate measurement machine (CMM) inspection report CMM-2022-07. Validation scope directly addresses the COU decision question. Achieved Gradation 2 meets MRL 2 requirement."
